data.title: Three swimmers win second U.S. Open gold medals as records fall
data.text:
Three more meet records fell on the third day of the U.S. Open Swimming Championships at the University of Minnesota Aquatic Center, and Kelsey Ditto, Mary DeScenza and Michael Klueh won their second gold medals of the week.

Klueh won the men's 400-meter freestyle in a meet-record time of 3 minutes, 47.62 seconds.

DeScenza won the women's 100 butterfly and set a meet record of 58.30 seconds.

Kohei Kawamoto reset the men's 100 butterfly meet record with a winning time of 51.71 seconds.

The championships continue through Saturday.

Cooper joins Wolves On the one-year anniversary of the blockbuster trade that sent Kevin Garnett to Boston, the Timberwolves on Thursday named Houston Rockets vice president of player personnel Dean Cooper to Randy Wittman's coaching staff. Cooper replaces Bob Ociepka, who accepted a job on new Chicago Bulls coach Vinny Del Negro's staff. Cooper spent nine seasons with the Rockets as a video coordinator/scout, assistant coach, NBA personnel scout and player personnel VP.

Fish to coach St. Cloud St. Cloud State named Lori Fish its women's basketball coach. Fish, who spent the past four seasons as the women's basketball coach at Minnesota State Mankato, replaces Lori Ulferts, who resigned in June.

Fish, a St. Cloud native who played collegiately at South Dakota State, served as an assistant to Ulferts from 1999 to 2004.

Minnesota State Mankato named Pam Gohl, who has been a Mavericks assistant the past two seasons, its interim head coach to replace Fish.

Etc. • Augsburg wrestling coach Sam Barber has resigned after one season as the Auggies coach. Assistant coach Mark Matzek was named interim head coach.

• The Wichita Wingnuts held on a for a 7-6 victory over the visiting St. Paul Saints on Thursday.

STAFF AND WIRE REPORTS

The official deadline for all teams to pick 53-man rosters is 3 p.m. on Aug. 27, and the clock is ticking in position battles at receiver, defensive line and defensive back.
